<section id="hephasto">
  <h2>Hephasto the Armorer</h2>
  <div class="images">
    <img src="images/hephasto_sprite.png" alt="Hephasto Classic Sprite">
    <img src="images/hephasto_render.png" alt="Hephasto D2R Render">
  </div>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Difficulty</th><th>Level</th><th>Health</th><th>Base Damage</th><th>Resistances</th><th>Abilities</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Normal</td><td>31</td><td>3,000</td><td>56–75</td><td>Fire 50%</td><td>Extra Strong, Cursed</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Nightmare</td><td>65</td><td>8,600</td><td>120–148</td><td>Fire 75%</td><td>Crushing Blow, high defense</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Hell</td><td>93</td><td>24,500</td><td>165–210</td><td>Fire 90%</td><td>Massive damage, immune to knockback</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <h3>Lore</h3>
  <p>Hephasto guards the Hellforge, where souls are bound and corrupted. A towering brute, his strikes can shatter bone and steel alike. Many have fallen trying to claim his forge hammer.</p>
  <h3>Notable Drops</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Normal:</strong> Hellforge quest rune (up to Amn), flails</li>
    <li><strong>Nightmare:</strong> Hellforge rune (up to Um), rare mauls</li>
    <li><strong>Hell:</strong> Hellforge rune (Gul–Ist), unique axes, socketed armor</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Affixes</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Prefix:</strong> Brutal – Increased damage output</li>
    <li><strong>Suffix:</strong> of Annihilation – Chance to cause explosion on kill</li>
  </ul>
</section>
<section id="diablo">
  <h2>Diablo, Lord of Terror</h2>
  <div class="images">
    <img src="images/diablo_sprite.png" alt="Diablo Classic Sprite">
    <img src="images/diablo_render.png" alt="Diablo D2R Render">
  </div>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Difficulty</th><th>Level</th><th>Health</th><th>Base Damage</th><th>Resistances</th><th>Abilities</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Normal</td><td>40</td><td>6,000</td><td>60–90</td><td>Fire 50%, Lightning 50%</td><td>Firestorm, Red Lightning Hose, Summons</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Nightmare</td><td>70</td><td>20,000</td><td>130–190</td><td>Fire 75%, Lightning 75%</td><td>Teleport, Fire Nova, Minion Spawns</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Hell</td><td>94</td><td>40,000</td><td>220–285</td><td>Fire 85%, Lightning 85%, Cold 33%</td><td>Massive AoE, Knockback, Fast Recovery</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <h3>Lore</h3>
  <p>The youngest of the Prime Evils, Diablo is the embodiment of fear and terror. Imprisoned beneath Tristram and then unleashed, he now rules the Chaos Sanctuary in Act IV, awaiting challengers to his throne.</p>
  <h3>Notable Drops</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Normal:</strong> Rare jewels, rings, and armor</li>
    <li><strong>Nightmare:</strong> Unique weapons, runes (Io–Um), high magic gear</li>
    <li><strong>Hell:</strong> Unique class-specific items, runes (Mal–Gul), elite armor and charms</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Affixes</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Prefix:</strong> Infernal – Fire enchanted burst</li>
    <li><strong>Suffix:</strong> of Terror – Fear aura drains stamina and defense</li>
  </ul>
</section>

</body>
<section id="act-v">
  <h1>Act V: Lord of Destruction</h1>
  <p>The frozen highlands of Mount Arreat harbor fierce and unrelenting enemies. From siege beasts to corrupted barbarians, each step toward the Worldstone Keep brings greater danger.</p>
</section>
